frameDefinitions: An Entity is in a specified State.
This frame concerns transparent nouns that denote Instances of Types of entities or events.
A Protagonist is in the dynamic, maintained state of being alive or has exited this state.
An Entity persists in a stable situation called a State
The words in this frame describe the death of a Protagonist.
frameExamples: Some of the classics were in excellent <t>condition</t>.

The survey confirmed that management interference in team operations had increased , and <t><fex name='Instance'>instances</fex></t> of management decisions being taken without team consultation had also increased .
The machine was not switched off, but Mr. Lavelle <t>died</t> of natural causes, police said.
listRoleDefinitions: The entity whose <fen>State</fen> is specified and/or evaluated.
A relation in which the <fen>Entity</fen> participates or a property that the <fen>Entity</fen> possesses.
A thing or episode of a certain <fen>Type</fen>.
The category of thing or event of which an <fen>Instance</fen> is picked out.
<fen>Protagonist</fen> identifies the being or entity that is  dead or alive.
This role identifies the <fen>Figure</fen> or form being described by the target.
The time in which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> is dead or alive.
The role <fen>Protagonist</fen> is the being or entity that dies.  With verbs in this frame, the <fen>Protagonist</fen> is the External Argument.
The role <fen>Time</fen> denotes when the dying or killing occurs.
The role <fen>Place</fen> indicates where the death takes place.
listRoleExamples: It was stressed that no diagnosis of <fex>my</fex> state of health would be made, so all she was doing was describing how she felt my 'aura' to be.
Despite being in a state <fex>of considerable disrepair</fex>, the building is surprisingly roomy inside and has a pleasant feel to it.
I collected two <t>specimens</t> <fex>of this rare species</fex>.
Your father passed away <fex>about four minutes ago</fex>.
Your father passed away <fex>in his hospital bed</fex>.
